  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nTake the following Goerli deployment for [`PRBProxyRegistry`](https://github.com/PaulRBerg/prb-proxy/blob/82d14b9d0b0f6be3df43268c41cffec4701368f8/src/PRBProxyRegistry.sol):\r\n\r\n- [0x33e200B5fb5e0C57d370d5202c26A35d07A46B98](https://goerli.etherscan.io/address/0x33e200B5fb5e0C57d370d5202c26A35d07A46B98#code)\r\n\r\nIn the \"Settings\" section, the following testing-related remappings will appear:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\"remappings\": [\r\n  \"@prb/test/=lib/prb-test/src/\",\r\n  \"ds-test/=lib/forge-std/lib/ds-test/src/\",\r\n  \"forge-std/=lib/forge-std/src/\",\r\n  \"prb-test/=lib/prb-test/src/\"\r\n],\r\n```\r\n\r\nForge includes these remappings in the standard JSON input used for verification on Etherscan because I have a `remappings.txt` file in the PRBProxy repo:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/PaulRBerg/prb-proxy/blob/82d14b9d0b0f6be3df43268c41cffec4701368f8/remappings.txt\r\n\r\nNow, I have an `optimized` profile in my `foundry.toml`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/PaulRBerg/prb-proxy/blob/82d14b9d0b0f6be3df43268c41cffec4701368f8/foundry.toml#L33-L37\r\n\r\nI tried adding this setting in there:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\nremappings = []\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith the goal of overriding the default remappings in `remappings.txt` and making Forge use these overridden remappings for verification. However, my plan didn't pan out - I ran `forge verify-contract` with the `--show-standard-json-input` flag, and the standard JSON input file that got generated continued to include the testing-related remappings from `remappings.txt`.\r\n\r\nThus, my feature request: allow us to override the remappings via the `remappings` field in `foundry.toml`.",
